case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Near complete or complete skeleton
case_circumstances: In 1995 there was a water leak under a pickers cabin.  The owner went down there to fix the leak and noticed a skeletal remains in a sleeping bag.  The coroner at the time made the removal and examined the body and cound not find a cause of death based on the condition of the body.  It appeared to be a hispanic male and they left the body in the cooler until I became coroner and decided to have an anthropologist examine the remains.  She found sharp force injuries in the C-1, C-2 region and confirmed that this was a homicide.
